HEADWORD: Thievery
<hw>Thiev"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
practice of stealing; theft; thievishness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Among the Spartans, <qex>thievery</qex> was a practice morally
good and honest.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is stolen.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thievish</ent>⟦br⟧
